To start the dev server, the user will have to run `aws sso login --profile soleil-dev` and `npx sst dev`. Assume we have done so, but if it seems like we haven't you can remind us to do so. Don't try to do it yourself.

When needed, you can search the codebases of the libaries we use, using your tools. This is your mcp file:
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "shadcn-ui-docs": { "url": "https://gitmcp.io/shadcn/ui" },
    "tanstack-router-and-start-docs": { "url": "https://gitmcp.io/TanStack/router" },
    "react-docs": { "url": "https://gitmcp.io/reactjs/react.dev" },
    "tailwindcss-docs": { "url": "https://gitmcp.io/tailwindlabs/tailwindcss" },
    "sst-docs": { "url": "https://gitmcp.io/sst/sst" }
  }
}

